litl
------------------------------------------
LiTL is a lightweight tool for recording events during the execution of
scientific high-performance applications. LiTL is designed to record events on
the user level only. Therefore, it consumes much less resources (CPU time,
memory, and the disk space) as the alternative tools, e.g. FxT that gather
events on both user and kernel levels. As a result, LiTL is well-suited for
recording events on embedded systems like ARM architectures.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  liblitl-devel-0.2-1bl1
  liblitl0-0.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.3-1
  cygport-0.37.4-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/trahay/LiTL

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/trahay/LiTL/archive/refs/tags/litl-0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack litl-0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./litl-0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/litl-0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/litl-0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblitl0-0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblitl-devel-0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(litl)
  /usr/bin/litl_merge.exe
  /usr/bin/litl_print.exe
  /usr/bin/litl_split.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/litl.README
  /usr/share/doc/litl/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/litl/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/litl/COPYRIGHT
  /usr/share/doc/litl/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/litl/README

(liblitl0)
  /usr/bin/cyglitl-0.dll

(liblitl-devel)
  /usr/include/litl_config.h
  /usr/include/litl_merge.h
  /usr/include/litl_read.h
  /usr/include/litl_split.h
  /usr/include/litl_timer.h
  /usr/include/litl_tools.h
  /usr/include/litl_types.h
  /usr/include/litl_write.h
  /usr/lib/liblitl.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/litl.pc

